###  https://www.w3id.org/climoo#ClimOO_0000076
:ClimOO_0000076 rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
                rdfs:subPropertyOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000175> ;
                owl:inverseOf :ClimOO_0000077 ;
                rdfs:domain _:genid1 ;
                rdfs:range _:genid5 ;
                <http://purl.org/dc/terms/source> """Primary works of reference: Calhau et al. (2023), Calhau et al. (2024, 2025), Heylighen et al. (2006), and Mitchell (2009).
Bibliography 
• Calhau, R. F., Almeida, J. P. A., Guizzardi, G., Hoffmann, R., Pires, L. F., Logan, J., & Moreira, J. R. (2025). Towards an Ontology of Type-Level Phenomena for System Modeling. In J. Grabis, T. E. J. Vos, M. J. Escalona, & O. Pastor (Eds.), Research Challenges in Information Science (Vol. 547, pp. 121–139). Springer Nature Switzerland. https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-92474-3_8

• Calhau, R. F., Prince Sales, T., Oliveira, Í., Kokkula, S., Ferreira Pires, L., Cameron, D., Guizzardi, G., & Almeida, J. P. A. (2024). A System Core Ontology for Capability Emergence Modeling. In H. A. Proper, L. Pufahl, D. Karastoyanova, M. Van Sinderen, & J. Moreira (Eds.), Enterprise Design, Operations, and Computing (Vol. 14367, pp. 3–20). Springer Nature Switzerland. https://doi.org/10.1007/978-3-031-46587-1_1

• Calhau, R., Sales, T. P., Almeida, J. P. A., & Guizzardi, G. (2023). Exploring system behavior in a system ontology. Int Conf Concept Model. 

• Heylighen, F., Cilliers, P., & Gershenson, C. (2006). Complexity and Philosophy. arXiv [Cs.CC]. 

• Mitchell, M. (2009). Complexity: A Guided Tour. Oxford University Press."""@en ;
                <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym> "has supersystemat some time"@en ;
                rdfs:comment """A subsystem is always a system that is a system component of another system, that, in turn, is intended as a supersystem for that first system. Whether interpreting a system as a super/subsystem or a component of another system depends on the perspective and the system scales used to analyze that system of interest.

We currently do not include direct reference to perspectives and system scales in the definition. Nevertheless, we strongly suggest expressing the perspective and system scales of reference by annotating axioms that cover this object property with the annotation property “according to the perspective” https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000039. 

We plan to implement the account of system scales and levels, ensuring a more adequate representation of these topics, especially concerning super/subsystems."""@en ,
                             "This is an initial attempt to represent the supersystem/subsystem-system interrelation. Further details may be required to implement this model, for instance, by considering aspects regarding functions of super/subsystems and systems or related interconnections."@en ;
                rdfs:label "is a subsystem of at some time"@en ;
                <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity> <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Provisional> ;
                <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/semiFormalNaturalLanguageDefinition> "b is a subsystem of a at some time t = Def for some time t ((a is a system) & (b is a system) & (b proper continuant part of a at t))."@en .

_:genid1 rdf:type owl:Class ;
          owl:unionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002577>
                        <https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000006>
                      ) .

_:genid5 rdf:type owl:Class ;
          owl:unionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002577>
                        <https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000006>
                      ) .

[ rdf:type owl:Axiom ;
   owl:annotatedSource :ClimOO_0000076 ;
   owl:annotatedProperty rdfs:domain ;
   owl:annotatedTarget _:genid1 ;
   rdfs:comment """ClimOO developer comment:
We extend the domain and range of this object property to “system environment” as considerations regarding systems equally apply to system environments.This supports also representing hierarchies of sub/super-systems across systems and related environments. Consider, for instance, cases when certain systems of interest are components of the system environments of other systems of interest, or when the system environment of a system of interest is another or part of another system interest."""@en
 ] .

[ rdf:type owl:Axiom ;
   owl:annotatedSource :ClimOO_0000076 ;
   owl:annotatedProperty rdfs:range ;
   owl:annotatedTarget _:genid5 ;
   rdfs:comment """ClimOO developer comment:
We extend the domain and range of this object property to “system environment” as considerations regarding systems equally apply to system environments.This supports also representing hierarchies of sub/super-systems across systems and related environments. Consider, for instance, cases when certain systems of interest are components of the system environments of other systems of interest, or when the system environment of a system of interest is another or part of another system interest."""@en
 ] .


###  https://www.w3id.org/climoo#ClimOO_0000077
:ClimOO_0000077 rdf:type owl:ObjectProperty ;
                rdfs:subPropertyOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000174> ;
                rdfs:domain _:genid9 ;
                rdfs:range _:genid13 ;
                <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym> "has subsystem at some time"@en ;
                rdfs:label "is a supersystem of at some time"@en ;
                rdfs:seeAlso "See comments to the inverse property \" is a subsystem of at some time\". https://www.w3id.org/climoo#ClimOO_0000076"@en ;
                <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity> <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Provisional> ;
                <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/semiFormalNaturalLanguageDefinition> "a is a supersystem of b at some time = Def b is a subsystem of a at some time t"@en .

