###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_24431
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/CHEBI_24431> rdfs:subClassOf [ rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                               owl:unionOf ( [ rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                               owl:unionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002577>
                                                                                             <https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000006>
                                                                                           )
                                                                             ]
                                                                             [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                               owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000176> ;
                                                                               owl:someValuesFrom [ rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                    owl:unionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002577>
                                                                                                                  <https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000006>
                                                                                                                )
                                                                                                  ]
                                                                             ]
                                                                           )
                                                             ] ;
                                             rdfs:comment """ClimOO Ontology developer comment:
Some of the entities referred to by subclasses of this class, such as atoms, monomers or polymers, can be interpreted as objects (BFO sense). For the purposes of the ClimOO Ontology, we currently reclassified as subclasses of the BFO “object” class only the “polymer”, “monomer”, “residue molecule of synthetic plastic manufacturing”, and “synthetic polymer-based material additive” classes."""@en ,
                                                          """ClimOO developer comment:
Currently, we included only main classes from ChEBI relevant for ClimOO purposes."""@en .


