Reference to supply chains and related activities may be added, as neeed."""@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_00010483
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_00010483> rdfs:subClassOf [ rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                 owl:unionOf ( [ rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                 owl:unionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000254>
                                                                                               :ClimOO_0000021
                                                                                             )
                                                                               ]
                                                                               [ rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                 owl:unionOf ( [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                 owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000176> ;
                                                                                                 owl:someValuesFrom [ rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                                      owl:unionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000254>
                                                                                                                                    :ClimOO_0000021
                                                                                                                                  )
                                                                                                                    ]
                                                                                               ]
                                                                                               [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                                 owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000176> ;
                                                                                                 owl:someValuesFrom [ rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                                      owl:unionOf ( :ClimOO_0000017
                                                                                                                                    :ClimOO_0000025
                                                                                                                                  )
                                                                                                                    ]
                                                                                               ]
                                                                                             )
                                                                               ]
                                                                             )
                                                               ] ;
                                               <http://www.ontologyrepository.com/CommonCoreOntologies/definition> """ClimOO Ontology revised definition:
A material entity which other material entities in an environmental system or its environment are primarily or partially composed of. Such a material entity and related entities that are primarily or partially composed of can be equally seen as an environmental system (or related environment) itself, depending on the endorsed perspective."""@en ;
                                               rdfs:comment """ClimOO Ontology developer comment:
Alignments with SCO opens questions regarding the scope of this class and the “mass of environmental material” class.  Is there anything that is not contained in an environmental system (or its environment)? Introduced axioms helps in addressing this issue. Is the proposed level of granularity adequate to effectively distinguish an environmental material from a related mass of environmental material? Given the subclasses included in EnvO, it does not seem to be always the case. Is it essential to introduce distinction between environmental materials and masses of environmental materials? Are “environmental material” classes needed and adequate to track material entity composition? A mass of environmental material is defined as “object that are discrete accumulations of environmental materials”. Is this characterization adequate to distinguish masses from aggregates? Are all masses (EnvO sense) objects, e.g. microplastics? We are inclined to think that the latter are objects (BFO sense) but it may not be always the case.Also, “environmental material” subclasses labels do not follow BFO and OBO-Foundry best practices. See Arp et al. (2015). We currently included those classes in the ClimOO Ontology. But we envision discussions with EnvO experts.
Arp, R., Smith, B., & Spear, A. D. (2015). Building ontologies with Basic Formal Ontology. Massachusetts Institute of Technology."""@en ,
                                                            """ClimOO developer comment:
According to EnvO, this class identifies materials entities that primarily or partially compose entities in an environmental system. To ensure adequate alignment between EnvO and SCO, for ClimOO Ontology purposes, we extend the coverage of this class. We intend this class to refer to material entities that primarily or partially compose entities in an environmental system or its related environment. Such entities, as well as those that primarily compose, can be, however, also considered as a system (or related environment), depending on the perspectives endorsed. Consider, for instance, a portion of soil. It can compose an entity that can be seen as part of an agricultural system (or its related system environment), or as a system itself (or its related system environment). Axioms restrict this class in such a way."""@en ;
                                               <https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000039> :ClimOO_0000072 .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000254
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000254> rdfs:subClassOf [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                 owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000086> ;
                                                                 owl:someValuesFrom <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000203>
                                                               ] ;
                                               owl:disjointWith :ClimOO_0000021 ;
                                               rdfs:comment """ClimOO developer comment:
For ClimOO purposes, we intend this class as a subclass of “complex system” class. If needed, this class can be generalized as a sibling class and a more specific class for environmental complex system may be created."""@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000281
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000281> rdfs:subClassOf [ rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                 owl:unionOf ( [ rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                 owl:unionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000254>
                                                                                               :ClimOO_0000021
                                                                                             )
                                                                               ]
                                                                               [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                 owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000176> ;
                                                                                 owl:someValuesFrom [ rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                      owl:unionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000254>
                                                                                                                    :ClimOO_0000021
                                                                                                                  )
                                                                                                    ]
                                                                               ]
                                                                             )
                                                               ] ;
                                               rdfs:comment """ClimOO developer comment:
Given EnvO definition, we interpret this class as referring strictly to environmental systems and related system environments and components. We envision having discussions with subject matter experts to confirm our interpretation and deepen account of (system) layers."""@en ,
                                                            """ClimOO developer comment:
See the comment to “environmental material” class. Same considerations apply here.
http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_00010483"""@en .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000313
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000313> owl:disjointWith :ClimOO_0000071 ;
                                               rdfs:comment """ClimOO developer comment:
We suggest to revise definitions of “anthropogenic environment” and “anthopised ecosystem” for consistently clarifying the two. ClimOO Ontology builds its representation on the latter as lowest leaf of the EnvO hierarchy."""@en .


