                                                                 owl:someValuesFrom :ClimOO_0000188
                                                               ] ;
                                               rdfs:comment """ClimOO Ontology developper comment:
Currently, the ClimOO Ontology imports EnvO representation of wastes and includes a class for plastic upcycling. This is adequate for current ontology purposes. Given the strict interconnection between upcycling and recycling processes, however, we envision discussions with subject matter expert for possible implementations."""@en .

[ rdf:type owl:Axiom ;
   owl:annotatedSource <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000741> ;
   owl:annotatedProperty rdfs:comment ;
   owl:annotatedTarget """ClimOO Ontology developper comment:
Currently, the ClimOO Ontology imports EnvO representation of wastes and includes a class for plastic upcycling. This is adequate for current ontology purposes. Given the strict interconnection between upcycling and recycling processes, however, we envision discussions with subject matter expert for possible implementations."""@en ;
   rdfs:comment "For insights on ongoing conversations on these topics see the “Food, Waste, and Sustainability: Synergizing Ontology Efforts” workshop at ICBO2025 https://sites.google.com/view/fws2025workshop/home-page"@en ;
   rdfs:seeAlso :ClimOO_0000178
 ] .


###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000776
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000776> rdfs:subClassOf [ owl:intersectionOf ( [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                        owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000086> ;
                                                                                        owl:someValuesFrom <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000052>
                                                                                      ]
                                                                                      [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                        owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000086> ;
                                                                                        owl:someValuesFrom <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000117>
                                                                                      ]
                                                                                      [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                                        owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000086> ;
                                                                                        owl:someValuesFrom [ rdf:type owl:Class ;
                                                                                                             owl:unionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000141>
                                                                                                                           <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0001332>
                                                                                                                         )
                                                                                                           ]
                                                                                      ]
                                                                                    ) ;
                                                                 rdf:type owl:Class
                                                               ] ,
                                                               _:genid94 ,
                                                               _:genid100 ,
                                                               [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                                                 owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0000091> ;
                                                                 owl:someValuesFrom <https://www.commoncoreontologies.org/ont00000378>
                                                               ] ;
                                               rdfs:comment """ClimOO Ontology developer comment:
According to the cited literature and the ontology hierarchy structure, we interpret EnvO “plastic particle” classes (subclasses of this class in envo, see https://www.ebi.ac.uk/ols4/ontologies/envo/classes/http%253A%252F%252Fpurl.obolibrary.org%252Fobo%252FENVO_01000776) as referring to plastic debris. Thus, we moved these classes under the upper-level class of “plastic debris particle”. In doing so, however, we extend coverage of these classes to litter that is, more broadly, made of synthetic polymer-based materials. For reference, see Hartmann et al. (2019).

Given the provided definitions and labels, these classes are ambiguous. They may solely refer to pieces of plastic of a certain size, not necessarily to debris. We opened a discussion on the EnvO repository to check whether our interpretation is correct. See here: https://github.com/EnvironmentOntology/envo/discussions/1636 
We also created specific classes to classify pieces of plastics based on their size. See subclasses.

Hartmann, N. B., Hüffer, T., Thompson, R. C., Hassellöv, M., Verschoor, A., Daugaard, A. E., Rist, S., Karlsson, T., Brennholt, N., Cole, M., Herrling, M. P., Hess, M. C., Ivleva, N. P., Lusher, A. L., & Wagner, M. (2019). Are We Speaking the Same Language? Recommendations for a Definition and Categorization Framework for Plastic Debris. Environmental Science & Technology, 53(3), 1039–1047. https://doi.org/10.1021/acs.est.8b05297"""@en ,
                                                            """ClimOO Ontology developer comment:
An object (BFO sense) made/constituted of some plastic material."""@en ,
                                                            """ClimOO Ontology developer comment:
Following EnvO representation, we intend the class “piece of plastic” as denoting generic identifiable causally unitary portions or fractions of (made of) plastic materials. This could be a fragment of natural or synthetic plastic material, or a plastic object, such as a plastic bottle. We aimed to ensure distinguishing between objects of daily usage and generic portions of plastics."""@en ,
                                                            """ClimOO Ontology developer comment:
Implementations require to address references to composition threshold. We envision discussion with subject matter experts."""@en ,
                                                            """ClimOO Ontology developer comment:
Not all plastics are solid and not under all conditions and temperatures. Thus, we reclassified this class as a direct subclass of the “mass of environmental material”. We assume that EnvO developers aimed to primarily account for plastic debris with these classes, that is, indeed, solid objects. For more details, see the plastic debris class and the following issue on the EnvO repo.
http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000776
https://github.com/EnvironmentOntology/envo/discussions/1636"""@en ,
                                                            """ClimOO Ontology developer comment:
This class and related subclasses  refer to the actual objects composed by some plastic materials, not to the constituting plastic materials or related polymers. This is in compliance with the literature and with EnvO approach.

The ClimOO Ontology distinguishes among the actual polymers (plastic polymers), the materials made of such polymers + additives etc. (plastic materials), and the objects/debris made of such plastic materials (pieces of plastic, and plastic litters)."""@en ,
                                                            """ClimOO Ontology developer comment:
We generalized this class to cover pieces of plastic in general, not ony made of synthetic plastic.  
According to EnvO original representation, we, instead, maintained EnvO subclasses solely referring to pieces made of synthetic plastic. This is currently sufficient for ClimOO Ontology purposes. Implementations can include corresponding classes for other types of plastics."""@en ,
                                                            "From a material science perspective (which is the one we have to refer to for classifying plastics and polymers) plastic materials are constituted by polymers that are thermosetting and thermoplastic, and not, for instance, by elastic polymers. There exist, however, some synthetic combinations, such as thermoplastic elastomer-based synthetic materials, that are composed by polymers presenting both elastic and plastic properties. Strictly speaking, the last are not plastics (material science perspective). However, these materials are included in the count of debris (from an environmental perspective which is the one we have to refer to for classifying debris and pollution). So, the ClimOO Ontology accounts for these two perspectives, modeling differences and interconnection."@en ;
                                               <https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000039> :ClimOO_0000072 ,
                                                                                      :ClimOO_0000073 ,
                                                                                      :ClimOO_0000074 ,
                                                                                      :ClimOO_0000075 ,
                                                                                      :ClimOO_0000228 .

