Reference to weight can be added as needed."""@en
 ] .

[ rdf:type owl:Axiom ;
   owl:annotatedSource <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000776> ;
   owl:annotatedProperty rdfs:comment ;
   owl:annotatedTarget """ClimOO Ontology developer comment:
Not all plastics are solid and not under all conditions and temperatures. Thus, we reclassified this class as a direct subclass of the “mass of environmental material”. We assume that EnvO developers aimed to primarily account for plastic debris with these classes, that is, indeed, solid objects. For more details, see the plastic debris class and the following issue on the EnvO repo.
http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000776
https://github.com/EnvironmentOntology/envo/discussions/1636"""@en ;
   <https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000039> :ClimOO_0000073
 ] .

[ rdf:type owl:Axiom ;
   owl:annotatedSource <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000776> ;
   owl:annotatedProperty rdfs:subClassOf ;
   owl:annotatedTarget _:genid94 ;
   rdfs:comment "We aim to establishing an initial account of plastic item surfaces in order to support the representation of pollutants sorption/release. We envision implementations."@en ;
   <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity> <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Provisional>
 ] .


