###  http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000944
<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000944> rdfs:subClassOf :ClimOO_0000234 ;
                                               owl:disjointWith <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_06105102> ,
                                                                <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_06105103> ,
                                                                <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_06105104> ,
                                                                <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_06105105> ,
                                                                :ClimOO_0000233 ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasBroadSynonym> "synthetic polymer debris microparticle"@en ;
                                               <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym> "microplastic debris, microplastic litter"@en ;
                                               rdfs:comment """ClimOO Ontology developer comment:
A possible way to align he two systems of classification concerning microplastic size ranges is to include a “large microplastic” class covering microplastic from 1 to 5 mm.
See, for instance, ISO/TR 21960:2020Plastics — Environmental aspects — State of knowledge and methodologies https://www.iso.org/standard/72300.html"""@en ,
                                                            """ClimOO Ontology developer:
EnvO considers 5 mm as the upper-level threshold to define microplastic particle, as this is a commonly recognized size edge in discussion on microplastic litter. Nevertheless, this is merely an operative definition and there is not complete consensus on employing it (Hartmann et a. 2019). Hartmann et al. (2019) proposes a range of 1-1000 micrometer. 
We included this EnvO class in the ClimOO Ontology specifying the lower-level threshold as 1 micrometer, and we further specialized it to distinguish when microplastic particles fall in the range 1 µm - 1 mm or that of 1 mm -5 mm."""@en ;
                                               <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> """Revised definition for ClimOO Ontology:
A plastic debris particle that is between 1 µm and 5 mm in its largest dimension."""@en ;
                                               <https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000039> :ClimOO_0000131 .

