                rdfs:comment """Definitions of plastic properties, such as biodegradability and composability, and related processes, currently covered in the ClimOO Ontology, refer to existing policy standards. This aims to stress the significance of such regulations concerning defining such entities and, especially, the consequences in terms of pollution and sustainability interventions.

It is noteworthy to mention that such standards present limitations. See, for instance, the work of Rayns et al. (2021), Steiner et al. (2022, 2024), concerning plastic biodegradability.

We envision implementing such definitions in accordance with regulation revisions and novel research findings."""@en ,
                             "Reference to anaerobic composting can be added as needed."@en ;
                rdfs:label "composting process"@en ;
                <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A biodegradation process that occurs in the presence of oxygen, has, as main input, some organic waste, and has, a main output, some compost.  (See EU EN 13432, UNI EN ISO 20200, and Regulation - 2023/2055 - EN - EUR-Lex)."@en ;
                <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity> <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Released> ;
