                <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A polymer that bears a disposition to be elastic (elasticity)."@en ;
                <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity> <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Released> .


###  https://www.w3id.org/climoo#ClimOO_0000126
:ClimOO_0000126 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                rdfs:subClassOf <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000016> ;
                <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasRelatedSynonym> "durability"@en ;
                rdfs:comment "We envision discussion with subject matter experts to implement the ClimOO Ontology representation of environmental persistence with regard to threshold, especially temporal thresholds." ;
                rdfs:label "environmental persistence"@en ;
                <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "An environmental disposition whose realization leads an environmental material to hold its qualities within the system (system environment) to which it belongs, for a period of time judged long enough according to some stakeholder perspective (metrics, standards)."@en ;
                <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity> <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Released> .


###  https://www.w3id.org/climoo#ClimOO_0000127
:ClimOO_0000127 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                rdfs:subClassOf :ClimOO_0000163 ;
                rdfs:label "film debris particle"@en ;
                <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A plastic debris particle that is flexible, thin, and planar."@en ;
                <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/adaptedFrom> "http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_06105007" ;
                <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity> <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Released> .


###  https://www.w3id.org/climoo#ClimOO_0000128
:ClimOO_0000128 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                rdfs:subClassOf :ClimOO_0000225 ,
                                [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
                                  owl:onProperty <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/RO_0002233> ;
                                  owl:someValuesFrom :ClimOO_0000150
                                ] ;
                rdfs:comment """Definitions of plastic properties, such as biodegradability and composability, and related processes, currently covered in the ClimOO Ontology, refer to existing policy standards. This aims to stress the significance of such regulations concerning defining such entities and, especially, the consequences in terms of pollution and sustainability interventions.

It is noteworthy to mention that such standards present limitations. See, for instance, the work of Rayns et al. (2021), Steiner et al. (2022, 2024), concerning plastic biodegradability.

We envision implementing such definitions in accordance with regulation revisions and novel research findings."""@en ,
                             "Reference to specific types of plastic materials and items can be added as needed."@en ,
                             "The hierarchy position of this class is to be further discussed."@en ;
                rdfs:label "fragmentation of a piece of synthetic polymer-based material"@en ;
                <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A process that leads to breaking down pieces of synthetic polymer-based material into pieces of a smaller size."@en ;
                <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity> <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Released> ;
                <https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000039> :ClimOO_0000072 ,
                                                       :ClimOO_0000073 ,
                                                       :ClimOO_0000074 ,
                                                       :ClimOO_0000075 ,
                                                       :ClimOO_0000228 .


