                                                     ) ;
                                  rdf:type owl:Class
                                ] ;
                rdfs:label "plastic composting process"@en ;
                <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A composting process that applies to polymers constituting the plastic of which some waste piece of biodegradable synthetic plastic, used as input or part of the input of this process, is made. Packaging applications: The pieces of biodegradable synthetic plastic must be broken down into particles smaller than 2 mm in their largest dimension within the first 12 weeks (according to EU EN 13432, standardized laboratory test conditions). Presence of heavy metals in the output compost must be below harmful levels with no negative consequences concerning agronomic value and plant growth ecotoxicity (See EU standard directly).  (See also UNI EN ISO 20200 and Regulation - 2023/2055 - EN - EUR-Lex)."@en ;
                <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity> <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Released> .


###  https://www.w3id.org/climoo#ClimOO_0000160
:ClimOO_0000160 rdf:type owl:Class ;
                owl:equivalentClass [ owl:intersectionOf ( <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/BFO_0000027>
                                                           [ rdf:type owl:Restriction ;
