                                ] ;
                <http://www.geneontology.org/formats/oboInOwl#hasExactSynonym> "release of plastic-carried pollutants"@en ;
                rdfs:comment "Pollutants may have synergizing or antagonizing effects on each other. We envision implementations to expand the representation in such a direction."@en ;
                rdfs:label "release of plastic debris-carried pollutants in the environment"@en ;
                <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> "A material transport process that has some synthetic polymer-based material (generally synthetic plastic) composing some plastic debris and having some pollutants as part, as participant, and, as output, 1) that synthetic polymer-based material with a decreased level of those pollutants as part, and 2) some other environmental material(s) with an increased level, equivalent to that of which synthetic polymer-based material decreases, of those pollutants (both compared to levels prior participating into that process)."@en ;
                <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/maturity> <https://spec.industrialontologies.org/ontology/core/meta/AnnotationVocabulary/Released> ;
                <https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000039> :ClimOO_0000072 ,
