<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_00002005> rdfs:comment """ClimOO developer comment:
Axioms detailing the additional elements that compose air may be reintroduced from EnvO, as needed."""@en .


<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_01000952> <http://www.ontologyrepository.com/CommonCoreOntologies/definition> """ClimOO developer comment:
It seems that there is some inconsistence with the use of the term “environment” and “ecosystem” in the definition of this class. The superclass refers to ecosystems. Here the focus is on natural environment. Currently, we maintain this class as it is. We, however, suggest revisions."""@en .


<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02000177> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> """ClimOO Ontology developer comment:
We included this class pertaining to the ClimOO Ontology domain of reference. Nevertheless, we envision implementations to further specify and develop it. Axiomatization seems requiring revisions."""@en .


<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500026> <http://www.ontologyrepository.com/CommonCoreOntologies/definition> """ClimOO Ontology revised definition:
A process during which human, part of an environmental system or its environment, apply technology to alter the magnitude, duration, rate, or impact of an environmental process."""@en ;
                                               rdfs:comment """ClimOO developer comment:
We consider this entire ontology branch identifying planned processes. Discussions are required whether only some should be considered as such."""@en ,
                                                            """ClimOO developer comment:
We currently leave open the discussion whether some of these processes should be considered complex system activities."""@en .


<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500027> <http://www.ontologyrepository.com/CommonCoreOntologies/definition> """ClimOO Ontology revised definition:
An environmental process which is driven by the action of humans (agent) part of that anthropogenic system or its environment."""@en ;
                                               rdfs:comment """ClimOO developer comment:
It seems that the definition of this class requires revisions to clarify reference to anthropogenic environment systems and anthropized ecosystems as well as to possibly align with related “environmental system process” and “ecosystem process” classes’ definitions."""@en ,
                                                            """ClimOO developer comment:
Reference to related system interactions can be added as needed. See the comment to the “environmental system process” class.
http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_02500000"""@en ,
                                                            """ClimOO developer comment:
We created a class specific to processes pertaining to anthopised ecosystem, considering this class as referring to environmental processing (EnvO-SCO aligned sense) generally driven by human action. This is our understanding from the definition and related subclasses. We made some revision to related hierarchies. We revised the definition to specify that we are referring to human part of the system or part of its environmental (this also applies to subclasses).

See https://www.w3id.org/climoo#ClimOO_0000065"""@en ,
                                                            """ClimOO developer comment:
We currently leave open the discussion whether some of these processes should be considered complex system activities."""@en .


<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_03501305> rdfs:comment """ClimOO Ontology developer comment:
This class seems requiring dismbiguation between the pliofilm material and the actual object."""@en .


<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_06105007> <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> """ClimOO Ontology revised definition:
A piece of synthetic plastic which is flexible, thin, and planar."""@en .


<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/ENVO_06105010> rdfs:label "debris particle of plastic pellet"@en ;
                                               <http://www.w3.org/2004/02/skos/core#definition> """ClimOO Ontology revised definition:
A piece of synthetic plastic which is 1) hard, 2) has a smooth external surface, and 3) has a roughly spherical or granular shape."""@en .


<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000009> rdfs:comment """ClimOO developer comment:
We constructed an initial alignment between IAO a CCO representation of ICE and measurements. It is tentative. We envision discussions with subject matter experts to revise and implement the work done so far."""@en ;
                                             rdfs:seeAlso """http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000583 
http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000039
http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000221""" .


<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/IAO_0000027> rdfs:comment """ClimOO developer comment:
We constructed an initial alignment between IAO a CCO representation of ICE and measurements. It is tentative. We envision discussions with subject matter experts to revise and implement the work done so far."""@en .


<http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/PATO_0000051> rdfs:comment """ClimOO ontology developer comment:
We included several subclasses for supporting extensions of this ontology towards specifying properties, such as different shapes of different pieces of plastic."""@en .


<http://purl.unep.org/sdg/SDGIO_00010071> rdfs:comment """ClimOO Ontology developer comment:
We included these classes for possible further implementations towards connecting plastic pollution and climate change to ecosystem services. We did not import the entire SDGIO representation that connects ecosystem services to natural capital and defines service providers and recipients. The ClimOO Ontology will incorporate corresponding classes as needed."""@en ,
                                                       """ClimOO developer comment:
For ClimOO Ontology purposes, according to implementation of the SDGIO “resource” class, we intend this class as referring to services that specifically pertain to environmental systems.
See also http://purl.unep.org/sdg/SDGIO_00000013""" .


<https://w3id.org/sumso#SuMSO_0000043> rdfs:comment """ClimOO developer comment:
Additional subclasses can be included to represent other supply chains and activities, pertaining to other systems, as needed. Similarly, some environmental processes can be classify as subclasses here or related to some activities, as neeed."""@en ,
                                                    """ClimOO developer comment:
ClimOO Ontology imports classes addressing supply chains and activities from SuMSO. Currently, the focus of these classes is restricted to supply chains and activities pertaining to the system of interest. They do not refer to supply chains and related activities pertaining to the related system environment. Implementations can be performed if needed."""@en .


<https://www.w3id.org/sco#SCO_0000041> rdfs:comment """ClimOO developer comment:
Some other ClimOO Ontology’s qualities and realizable entities can be further included as subclasses here, if needed."""@en .


